.\" Ralphglasses manual page
.\" Format: troff/groff man page
.\" Render with: man ./ralphglasses.1
.TH RALPHGLASSES 1 "2026-03-22" "ralphglasses dev" "Ralphglasses Manual"
.
.SH NAME
ralphglasses \- command-and-control TUI for parallel LLM agent loops
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ralphglasses
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B ralphglasses mcp
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B ralphglasses completion
\fISHELL\fR
.br
.B ralphglasses version
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ralphglasses
is a k9s-style terminal user interface for managing parallel LLM agent loops
(ralph loops) across multiple repositories.
It supports Claude Code, Gemini CLI, and OpenAI Codex CLI as session providers.
.PP
Ralphglasses scans a directory tree for ralph-enabled repositories
(those containing a \fB.ralph/\fR directory or a \fB.ralphrc\fR file),
then presents a live dashboard of their status.
Loops can be started, stopped, and paused without leaving the TUI.
.PP
Ralphglasses is also an MCP server (see \fBmcp\fR subcommand) exposing 126 tools
for programmatic orchestration by an LLM.
.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-scan\-path " DIR"
Root directory to scan for ralph-enabled repos.
Default: \fB~/hairglasses-studio\fR.
Supports tilde expansion.
.TP
.BI \-\-theme " NAME"
Color theme for the TUI.
Built-in themes: \fBk9s\fR (default), \fBdracula\fR, \fBgruvbox\fR, \fBnord\fR.
May also be a path to a YAML theme file.
.TP
.B \-\-notify
Enable desktop notifications for critical alerts
(e.g., circuit breaker opening, loop crash).
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version, commit, and build date, then exit.
.TP
.B \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help text and exit.
.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.SS mcp
.B ralphglasses mcp
[\fB\-\-scan\-path\fR \fIDIR\fR]
.PP
Run ralphglasses as an MCP (Model Context Protocol) server over stdio.
The server exposes 126 tools for managing ralph loops and LLM sessions.
Clients connect via JSON-RPC over stdin/stdout.
.PP
The \fB\-\-scan-path\fR flag is inherited from the root command.
Alternatively, set the \fBRALPHGLASSES_SCAN_PATH\fR environment variable.
.PP
Codex-first repo-local MCP/client setup is already configured via \fB.codex/config.toml\fR and \fB.mcp.json\fR.
Other MCP clients can register the same command explicitly if needed:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
go run . mcp --scan-path ~/projects
.fi
.RE
.PP
A \fB.mcp.json\fR and \fB.codex/config.toml\fR in the repo root enable automatic local discovery
when Codex or another compatible MCP client is opened from the ralphglasses directory.
.
.SS completion
.B ralphglasses completion
\fISHELL\fR
.PP
Generate shell completion scripts.
\fISHELL\fR must be one of: \fBbash\fR, \fBzsh\fR, \fBfish\fR.
.PP
Example (bash):
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
ralphglasses completion bash > /etc/bash_completion.d/ralphglasses
.fi
.RE
.PP
Example (zsh):
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
ralphglasses completion zsh > "${fpath[1]}/_ralphglasses"
.fi
.RE
.
.SS version
.B ralphglasses version
.PP
Print the version string, git commit SHA, and build date, then exit.
When built from source without ldflags, reports \fBdev\fR / \fBunknown\fR.
.PP
To embed version information at build time:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
go build \\
  -ldflags "-X main.version=$(git describe --tags) \\
            -X main.commit=$(git rev-parse HEAD) \\
            -X main.buildDate=$(date -u +%Y-%m-%d)" \\
  -o ralphglasses .
.fi
.RE
.
