.SH FILES
.TP
.I .ralphrc
Per-repository configuration file.
Shell-style \fBKEY="value"\fR format.
Keys must match \fB[A-Z_][A-Z0-9_]*\fR.
See \fBCONFIGURATION\fR below.
.TP
.I .ralph/status.json
Loop status written by the ralph loop on each iteration.
Fields: \fBtimestamp\fR, \fBloop_count\fR, \fBcalls_made_this_hour\fR,
\fBmax_calls_per_hour\fR, \fBlast_action\fR, \fBstatus\fR, \fBexit_reason\fR,
\fBnext_reset\fR, \fBmodel\fR, \fBsession_spend_usd\fR, \fBbudget_status\fR.
.TP
.I .ralph/progress.json
Task progress written by the ralph loop.
Fields: \fBspec_file\fR, \fBiteration\fR, \fBcompleted_ids\fR,
\fBlog\fR, \fBstatus\fR, \fBstarted_at\fR, \fBupdated_at\fR.
.TP
.I .ralph/.circuit_breaker_state
Circuit breaker state (JSON).
Fields: \fBstate\fR (CLOSED/HALF_OPEN/OPEN), \fBlast_change\fR,
\fBconsecutive_no_progress\fR, \fBconsecutive_same_error\fR,
\fBconsecutive_permission_denials\fR, \fBlast_progress_loop\fR,
\fBtotal_opens\fR, \fBreason\fR, \fBcurrent_loop\fR, \fBopened_at\fR.
.TP
.I .ralph/ralphglasses.pid
PID of the ralph loop process started by ralphglasses.
Created on loop start, removed on clean exit.
Used to re-adopt surviving processes after a ralphglasses restart.
.TP
.I .ralph/logs/
Directory for loop log files.
Rotated based on \fBLOG_RETENTION_DAYS\fR.
.TP
.I .ralph/improvement_journal.jsonl
Append-only JSONL improvement journal.
One entry per session, recording what worked, failed, and suggestions.
.TP
.I .ralph/PROMPT.md
System prompt for the ralph agent.
Created by \fBralphglasses_repo_scaffold\fR.
.TP
.I .ralph/fix_plan.md
Markdown task list the agent works through.
Created by \fBralphglasses_repo_scaffold\fR.
.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The \fB.ralphrc\fR file uses shell-style \fBKEY="value"\fR syntax.
Comments start with \fB#\fR.
.PP
Keys recognized by the ralph loop:
.TP
.B MAX_CALLS_PER_HOUR
Maximum Claude API calls per hour (default: 80).
.TP
.B CLAUDE_TIMEOUT_MINUTES
Timeout per Claude invocation in minutes (default: 20).
.TP
.B SESSION_CONTINUITY
Resume previous session ID between iterations (default: true).
.TP
.B CB_NO_PROGRESS_THRESHOLD
Open circuit after N no-progress loops (default: 4).
.TP
.B CB_SAME_ERROR_THRESHOLD
Open circuit after N identical errors (default: 5).
.TP
.B CB_PERMISSION_DENIAL_THRESHOLD
Open circuit after N permission denials (default: 2).
.TP
.B CB_COOLDOWN_MINUTES
Minutes before auto-reset attempt (default: 15).
.TP
.B CB_AUTO_RESET
Automatically attempt circuit reset after cooldown (default: true).
.PP
Keys used by \fBmarathon.sh\fR supervisor (not read by ralph itself):
\fBMARATHON_DURATION_HOURS\fR,
\fBMARATHON_CHECKPOINT_INTERVAL\fR,
\fBRALPH_SESSION_BUDGET\fR.
.PP
See \fBdocs/examples/ralphrc-full\fR for a fully commented example.
.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B RALPHGLASSES_SCAN_PATH
Default scan path, overrides the compiled-in default.
Overridden by \fB\-\-scan\-path\fR flag.
.TP
.B ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
API key for Claude Code.
Omit if using Claude Code OAuth (\fBclaude login\fR).
Setting this when OAuth is active causes auth conflicts.
.TP
.B GOOGLE_API_KEY
API key for Gemini CLI.
.TP
.B OPENAI_API_KEY
API key for OpenAI Codex CLI.
.TP
.B CLAUDECODE
Set by Claude Code to prevent nested sessions.
Unset before launching headless claude sessions from scripts.
.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Start the TUI
.nf
ralphglasses --scan-path ~/projects
.fi
.SS Start with a custom theme
.nf
ralphglasses --scan-path ~/projects --theme dracula
.fi
.SS Run as MCP server with custom scan path
.nf
ralphglasses mcp --scan-path ~/projects
.fi
.SS Run MCP server with explicit scan path
.nf
RALPHGLASSES_SCAN_PATH=~/projects go run /path/to/ralphglasses mcp
.fi
.SS Generate bash completions
.nf
ralphglasses completion bash > /etc/bash_completion.d/ralphglasses
.fi
.SS Scaffold a new repo for ralph
.nf
# Via MCP (for Codex, Claude Code, or another MCP client):
# ralphglasses_repo_scaffold {"repo_path": "/path/to/repo"}
.fi
.
